  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Human Security and Community Stabilisation</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of the project is to address human security indicators in order to increase stability and social cohesion in the region of Borkou (Chad). To achieve this objective, the project is built on three main pillars. The project aims to strengthen social and community security in Faya by supporting the community with the rehabilitation of a transit centre for stranded migrants through participatory capacity building schemes for youth.  The project will also help to strengthen food security by reinforcing livelihood opportunities in Faya and will contribute to gender equality and economic and environmental security by strengthening opportunities for women cooperatives through community farming.</narrative>
  </description>
